tachyon.client.file

Class FileOutStream

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.io.OutputStream
      • tachyon.client.file.FileOutStream
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Closeable, Flushable, AutoCloseable, Cancelable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DummyFileOutputStream, LineageFileOutStream

    @PublicApi
public class FileOutStream
extends OutputStream
implements Cancelable
    Provides a streaming API to write a file. This class wraps the BlockOutStreams for each of the blocks in the file and abstracts the switching between streams. The backing streams can write to Tachyon space in the local machine or remote machines. If the UnderStorageType is SYNC_PERSIST, another stream will write the data to the under storage system.

        Description copied from interface: Cancelable
        Cancels the write to Tachyon storage. This will delete all the temporary data and metadata that has been written to the worker(s). This method should be called when a write is aborted.
